  "footnotes": [
    "Empire of Nicaea (1204–1261): Exiled Byzantine court in northwestern Anatolia; recaptured Constantinople in 1261 and restored the Palaiologos dynasty.",
    "Empire of Trebizond (1204–1461): Byzantine successor state on the Black Sea coast of Anatolia; not within the Greek peninsula but a co-claimant to Byzantine legitimacy.",
    "Duchy of Athens passed from de la Roche to the Catalan Company (1311–1388), then to the Acciaioli (1388–1458), before Ottoman conquest.",
    "Venice retained the Ionian Islands (Corfu, Zakynthos, Cephalonia) until 1797 (Treaty of Campo Formio); they passed to France, then Britain, and joined Greece in 1864.",
